 Famous Nigerian comic actor and skit maker, Debo Adedayo, known by his stage name Mr Macaroni has taken to social media to speak against the killing of a level 200 student of Shehu Shagari College of Education Sokoto for allegedly blaspheming Prophet Muhammad. The news of the killing of a Christian girl who is a level 200 student of Shehu Shagari College of Education Sokoto for allegedly blaspheming Prophet Muhammad has taken the Nigerian social space by storm with scores speaking hard against the government to seek justice for the victim. Adding his voice to the many that have risen in seeking justice for the poor girl, Mr Macaroni wrote that everyone has the right to live and as such nothing grants the other person the privileged to kill in the name of defending their religion. “Every citizen has a right to life! No person or group of persons has the right to take the life of another citizen!11 You cannot kill another in the name of defending your religion. Do we all start killing ourselves in the name of religions?? it is inhumane and it must end”, he tweeted. 